            <strong>4. COOKIES</strong>
            <p>As you navigate through our website and Apps, certain information can be passively collected (that is, gathered without your actively providing the information) using various technologies and means, such as Internet Protocol addresses, cookies, Internet tags, and navigational data collection.</p>
            <p></p>
            <p>A "cookie" is a bit of information that an App sends to your web browser that helps the site remember information about you and your preferences. It is used to identify yourself to an App when you revisit it, to load your preferences and to track the pages you have visited. The only personal information held in such a cookie is information you have provided to Psycho Technology. You have the choice of whether or not to accept cookies using your browser settings, although you may not be able to use certain features and functionalities of the app if you do disable them.</p>
            <p></p>
            <p>This App may use Internet Protocol (IP) addresses. We use your IP address to diagnose problems with our server, report aggregate information, determine the fastest route for your computer to use in connecting to our App, and administer and improve services to our consumers.</p>
            <p></p>
            <p>"Session cookies" are temporary bits of information that are erased once you exit your web browser window or otherwise turn your computer off. Session cookies are used to improve navigation on App's and to collect aggregate statistical information. This App uses session cookies.</p>
            <p></p>
            <p>"Persistent cookies" are more permanent bits of information that are placed on the hard drive of your computer and stay there unless you delete the cookie. Persistent cookies store information on your computer for some purposes, such as retrieving certain information you have previously provided (e.g., username), helping to determine what areas of the App visitors find most valuable, and customizing the App based on your preferences. This App uses persistent cookies.</p>
            <p></p>
            <p>"Internet tags" (also known as single-pixel GIFs, clear GIFs, invisible GIFs, and 1-by-1 GIFs) are smaller than cookies and tell the App server information such as the IP address and browser type related to the visitor's computer. This App uses Internet tags.</p>
            <p></p>
            <p>"Navigational data" ("log files," "server logs," and "clickstream" data) and "Internet Tags" are used for system management, to improve the content of the site, market research purposes, and to communicate information to visitors. This App uses navigational data.</p>
